    "About 44.4% of the datasets were from systematic reviews, while the remaining 55.6% were from systematic reviews with meta-analyses.",
    "The research syntheses covered various topics, including factors affecting student learning (29.6%); teacher training, competence, and attitudes (22.2%); educational policies and interventions (22.2%); instructional design (14.8%); and bibliographic analyses of research methods and data (11.1%).",
    "They also targeted a wide range of research methods, such as mixed methods (48.2%), correlational studies (40.7%), and experimental studies (11.1%).",
    "The main samples of the study were K-12 students (42.3%), teachers (23.1 %), P-20 (15.4%), researchers (11.5%), and university students (7.7%).",
